metadatas.description: This is Short Description: Pachinko is an American drama television series created by Soo Hugh based on the 2017 novel by Min Jin Lee. The series premiered on Apple TV+ on March 25, 2022. It received critical acclaim, particularly for its cinematography, writing, and the performances of the cast. The second season premiered on August 23, 2024.
metadatas.long_description: This is Long Description: The narrative begins in 1915 Yeongdo, a small island of the second largest city Busan, in Japanese-occupied Korea with Yangjin, evidently in some anguish, visiting a female shaman's house, where Yangjin recounts that she is married to a kind man with a cleft-lip with whom she has born three sons, none of whom have lived beyond one year, and asks the shaman to 'lift the curse' of her childbearing. The narrative jumps to 1989 in New York City, where it follows a young, sharply-dressed Korean-American business man, who we later learn is originally from Japan and is named Solomon, as he attends a performance-review meeting with two of his managers, who inform him that, despite his stellar performance, he has not been selected by executives for a promotion to Vice President, news that prompts Solomon to boldly propose in the meeting that he be sent to Japan in order to close a stalled business deal worth millions of dollars, since he is confident he can cajole a Korean woman who is holding up the deal, in order to secure for himself the promotion and pay raise he covets.
metadatas.season_title: Season 2 - The lady in the Scarlet
metadatas.cast: Linda Cam, Hieu Minh, Tran My Bui, Jackfive, MiuVilla, Rose Back, Jacob William, Lee Min Sung, Han Chi Mi

metadatas.title: Secret Forest Documentary
metadatas.description: Short Description: Explore the hidden depths of the world's most ancient forests and the creatures that call them home.
metadatas.long_description: Long Description: This documentary uncovers the mysteries of the forest, from the towering trees to the microscopic organisms that thrive in the rich ecosystem. Viewers will discover the hidden layers of life within the oldest forests on Earth.

metadatas.title: Samurai History Documentary
metadatas.description: Short Description: Journey through the final days of the samurai, exploring their code of honor and way of life.
metadatas.long_description: Long Description: This historical documentary focuses on the end of the samurai era in Japan, tracing the lives of key figures who fought to preserve their traditions. Through dramatic reenactments and expert commentary, viewers will experience the samurai's battles, sacrifices, and legacy.
metadatas.season_title: Season 1 - The Fall of the Samurai

data.title_of_video: Playlist Title: Wonders of the World

metadatas.title: Great Wall Documentary
metadatas.description: Short Description: Discover the history and secrets behind one of the greatest architectural feats in human history, the Great Wall of China.
metadatas.long_description: Long Description: Spanning over 13,000 miles, the Great Wall of China is a symbol of China's enduring strength. This documentary delves into its construction, the dynasties that built it, and the soldiers who defended it, revealing the wall's place in history.

metadatas.title: Ice Age Documentary
metadatas.description: Short Description: Travel back in time to the Ice Age, when glaciers covered much of the Earth and giant mammals roamed the land.
metadatas.long_description: Long Description: This documentary transports viewers to a time when ice dominated the planet, exploring the lives of woolly mammoths, saber-toothed cats, and early humans. Learn how these creatures adapted to the harsh climate and the impact of the Ice Age on today's world.

metadatas.title: Solar System Documentary
metadatas.description: Short Description: A captivating exploration of our solar system, from the Sun to the distant icy planets.
metadatas.long_description: Long Description: Join astronomers and scientists as they take you on a journey through our solar system. From the burning core of the Sun to the mysterious outer planets, discover the wonders and dangers that exist in the vast space around us.

metadatas.title: Ancient Egypt Documentary
metadatas.description: Short Description: Uncover the mysteries of ancient Egypt, from the building of the pyramids to the reign of the pharaohs.
metadatas.long_description: Long Description: Explore the fascinating history of ancient Egypt, a civilization known for its monumental architecture, complex religion, and powerful rulers. This documentary examines the lives of the pharaohs, the secrets of the pyramids, and the culture that has captivated the world for centuries.

data.title_of_program: Title: The Rise of the Dragon Empire

metadatas.title: Dragon Empire Documentary
metadatas.description: Short Description: This documentary explores the rise and fall of the mythical Dragon Empire, examining its legendary rulers and fearsome warriors.
metadatas.long_description: Long Description: In the year 1000, a great empire arose from the East, its armies led by the legendary Dragon Emperor. This documentary delves deep into the history of the empire, tracing its path from a small kingdom to a sprawling domain.

metadatas.title: Space Explorers Documentary
metadatas.description: Short Description: Follow a team of astronauts as they journey into the unknown, seeking to uncover the mysteries of space.
metadatas.long_description: Long Description: In this thrilling documentary, viewers are taken on a journey beyond the stars, exploring distant planets and galaxies. Led by an experienced team of astronauts, the mission uncovers never-before-seen phenomena and the wonders of the universe.
